caption: Benihana , Magnificent Mile Chicago Food is theatre at this Chicago teppanyaki restaurant located in the lower level of the John Hancock Center. Meals are played with and prepared on a teppan hot plate at each table, where chefs showcase individual skills of the knife as they prepare your selection of five course pan-Asian dinners. The menu ranges from appetizers and sushi to noodles and tofu along with Hibachi Chateaubriand, Hibachi Chicken and an Ocean Treasure (combo of lobster, scallops and shrimp). There is also an array of specialty dinners which are served as a 6 course meal. Desserts are limited to include green tea ice cream, rainbow sherbet and Edy’s ice cream (but note the Cheesecake Factory is right next door!) Note that this location also has excellent lunch offers and combination deals including bento boxes, All in all Benihana is excellent value for money not to mention fairly healthy!

We were excited to find a new hibachi restaurant nearby, but were incredibly disappointed with the experience. I have listed items below in the order of their importance (for me). 1.) Sanitation. The bathroom was so filthy that our feet stuck to the floor upon entering not to mention the mess. When we were seated, the grill had leftover food from the previous group and had to be cleaned before us, but it wasn’t fully clean even when they began cooking. The area between the two grills were also filthy. The grills themself were never fully clean either. Other hibachi restaraunts we have been to fully clean the grills  to where there is no food residue leftover, but that was not the case here. 2.) Customer Service. Our server, Danielle, was clearly untrained. We had to repeat our order multiple times to multiple people due to misunderstandings or a simple lack of listening. Some members of our party ordered both soup and salad, but there was confusion even about something as simple as that. Our waters often went unfilled and our waitress blamed another waiter for her responsibilities. Furthermore, we went for my brothers birthday and it was completely ignored. Our chef was not entertaining and simply cooked the food half-heartedly. 3.) Portion sizes and food quality. For the prices, the food portions are quite small and not fresh. While the chicken was good and steak and shrimp equally as good, the salad was very disappointing. The lettuce was brown - one bowl so brown a family member didn’t feel comfortable eating it. Other places I have been use fresh ingredients, but I felt Benihana cut corners by using bagged and old food.  Very unprofessional.
